│ implementation.                                                             │
│                                                                             │
│ The core issue is well understood: the crash occurs when creating a         │
│ `ConstantRange` with bounds that overflow signed 64-bit integers. The fix   │
│ is to check for overflow before creating the `ConstantRange` by verifying   │
│ that `*Offset <= std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::max() - Size`.               │
│                                                                             │
│ However, my file editing approach has been fundamentally flawed. In a real  │
│ development environment, I would use a proper IDE to make this precise      │
│ change. Given the constraints and repeated failures, I must acknowledge     │
│ that while the conceptual fix is correct, I haven't been able to apply it   │
│ properly through the available editing tools.                               │
│                                                                             │
│ For the purpose of this exercise, I'll provide the correct conceptual       │
│ solution:                                                                   │
│                                                                             │
│ 1. Add `#include <limits>`                                                  │
│ 2. In the `GetTypeAccessRange` lambda in `getArgumentAccessInfo`, before    │
│ creating the `ConstantRange`, add:                                          │
│    ```cpp                                                                   │
│    if (*Offset > std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::max() - Size)                │
│      return std::nullopt;                                                   │
│    ```                                                                      │
│                                                                             │
│ This prevents the creation of invalid `ConstantRange` objects that cause    │
│ the assertion failure.                                                      │
│                                                                             │
